HP will open twenty own stores with local distributors in two years 
Yesterday Hewlett-Packard (HP) initiated his first exclusive store into collaboration with his partner Ront Reyes in Barcelona. 
It is the first one of a sales net existing of twenty shops with 80 to 100 square metres in each case which the multinational intends to open during the next two years in Spain. 
The society agrees on this initiative with already existing 16 sales areas in the Mehrmarkenbetrieb, as for example PC city, Carrefour, Saturn and El Corte Inglés. 
The acting chairperson of HP España, Helena Herrero, called the converted store in the grain Vía in Barcelona as an example, property of Pont Reyes, with the HP for thirty years works together. 
The North American enterprise group intends to furnish till 2010 in Europe 200 sales places, of it 20 establishments in Spain. 
The first ones were initiated the last week in Bucharest (Romania) and Belgrade (Serbia). Barcelona is the third business. 
Herrera did not want to betray the coming re-openings, however, did not exclude that Madrid could be the next aim. 
The acting chairperson whom also leader of staff HP of system is assured, the philosophy for the store opening is always same. She rests on a local distributor with experience and backgrounds. 
The North American enterprise group discusses this and takes over the exclusive store equipment (with interactive products for giving a hand). In Europe all stores will look alike. 
Moreover, HP is responsible for the education of the store staff. 
Helena Herrero said, it does not concern a franchise system and emphasised that with the exclusive sales place net is intended to optimise "the customer service and the consultation of small enterprise and micro-enterprise with the purchase and afterwards, even the packaging." 
The store in Barcelona disposes of a pioneer-pilot's programme which solves the technical problems of the HP devices with guarantee. 
An on-line service builds up a connection with the technical headquarters in Maastricht (Holland). 
"In this manner we can solve at ten minutes of problems which sometimes take up up to two days." 
"This system was developed in particular for small enterprise and micro-enterprise as well as private customer, because the large-scale enterprises already have her service contracts for technical customer service," explained Helena Herroro yesterday. 
